Iran: Campaign to free jailed student photographer=20

Roisin Joyce*
More than 70 Iranian graduates have launched a campaign calling for the
release of their friend and colleague, student photographer Hamed Saber,
http://www.rferl.org/content/Free_Hamed_Saber_Campaign_Supports_Photographe=
r_Arrested_Over_Protest_Pix/2102988.html
reported last month. Saber was arrested on 21 June and there had been no
communication regarding his whereabouts.
Full report on the University World News site:
http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=3D20100806172552207
