UNI-LATERAL: Off-beat university stories
---------------------------------------------------------------------------

N IGERIA: Controversy over student dress codes

Tunde Fatunde
A debate in N igeria over student dress codes rages on =96 running the gamut
from student academic achievement, discipline, professionalism, conformity
with social mores and clothes-as-political-statement to consumerism. While
some university authorities argue that mode of dress is an important factor
in determining student success or failure and should thus be subject to
rules, others =96 especially in the humanities and social sciences =96 rema=
in
unconvinced.
Full report on the University World News site:
http://www.universityworldnews.com/article.php?story=3D2010080617134822
